7. ApplicationStarted/ApplicationReady events fired — user code can listen.
8. Application runs, handling requests through DispatcherServlet → controllers.


Flow of a REST Service (request → response)
1. Client sends HTTP request.
2. Network/Load Balancer → hits application instance.
3. Servlet Container receives request; DispatcherServlet (Spring MVC) receives it.
4. HandlerMapping finds Controller method (based on @RequestMapping, HTTP verb).
5. Interceptors / Filters run (preHandle).
    1. Controller method executes — calls Service layer → Repository/DAO layer to access DB.
6. Service returns DTO; Controller returns ResponseEntity (status + body).
7. HTTP Message Converters serialize object to JSON (Jackson).
8. Interceptors / Filters (postHandle, afterCompletion) run, response is sent.
9. Client receives response.



